1. The statement is false because most menu prices already include taxes, so there's no tax to tip on.
2. The statement is false because the service charge already included in the menu price serves the same purpose as a tip, making an additional tip unnecessary.
3. The statement is false because it's customary to tip in addition to the service charge, not the tax, as the tax is already included in the menu price.
4. The statement is false because it implies that the tax and the tip are two separate amounts, when in fact the tax is already a part of the menu price.